25|$|A special miracle recounted by Fr. Romano to Fr. Diego de la Torre, {{who added}} {{that there were many}} {{witnesses}} to this prodigy. During Holy Week of 1739, a native from Piat was crossing the river beside the Ermita when he was caught by a crocodile. Placed in this situation, he invoked Our Lady of Piat, and was immediately free of the animal's jaws. <b>The</b> <b>poor</b> <b>man,</b> shaking violently, went to the Ermita to thank Our Lady.|$|E
