60|$|In one word, {{while the}} spirit of the world thinks of itself, and helps itself, Charity, which is the Spirit of God, thinks of other people, and helps other people. And now:--to be always {{thinking}} of other people's feelings, and always caring for other people's comfort, what is that but the mark, and the only mark, of a true gentleman, and a true lady? There is none other, my friends, and there never will be. But <b>the</b> <b>poorest</b> <b>man</b> or woman can do that; <b>the</b> <b>poorest</b> <b>man</b> or woman can be courteous and tender, careful not to pain people, ready and willing to help every one {{to the best of their}} power; and therefore, <b>the</b> <b>poorest</b> <b>man</b> or woman can be a true gentleman or a true lady in the sight of God, by the inspiration of the Spirit of God, whose name is Charity.|$|R
